'''John Peter Novembre''' (b. {{Birth based on age as of date|37|2015|09|28|noage=1}}) is a [[computational biologist]] at the [[University of Chicago]]. He received a [[MacArthur Fellowship]] in 2015. Novembre has developed [[data visualization]] and [[data analysis|analysis]] techniques to investigate correlations between [[genomic]] diversity, geography, and [[demographic]] structure.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.macfound.org/fellows/942/ |title=John Novembre — MacArthur Foundation |publisher=MacArthur Foundation  |date=  |author= |accessdate= September 29, 2015}}</ref>

== Education ==
Novembre completed his undergraduate education in [[biochemistry]] at [[Colorado College]] in 2000.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://jnpopgen.org|title=Novembre Lab - Home|website=jnpopgen.org|access-date=2018-01-08}}</ref> He then received a [[PhD]] in [[population genetics]] in 2006 at [[UC Berkeley]]; he was supervised by [[Montgomery Slatkin]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://jnpopgen.org/team/|title=Novembre Lab - Team|website=jnpopgen.org|access-date=2018-01-08}}</ref> He then went on to do postdoctoral research with [[Matthew Stephens (statistician)|Matthew Stephens]] in Chicago.<ref name=":0" /> In 2008, Novembre joined the Department of Ecology and Evolutionary Biology at the [[University of California, Los Angeles]].<ref>https://www.eeb.ucla.edu/Faculty/Novembre/JN_CV_web.pdf</ref>

